content.description: The crux is definitely the start. Just clip the second bolt after you get up to the shelf and pump through and find your feet through to the 3rd bolt.
content.location: 1 route to the left of Dave's Not Here (5.11b). It's hard to spot. You'll need a guide book or pic to find it.

content.description: Cool route through two big huecos. Neat crux comes shortly after.

*** Route name may have changed, this is the name as in my version of the guidebook (listed as expired project, 4 bolts, 5.hard) ***

  Gain the ledge, unprotected, to clip the 1st bolt (the tree stump may be used to make this easier.) Bouldery moves lead past the 2nd bolt to a cave where the 3rd bolt may be clipped. Top section is thin, find good feet to advance to the next bolt. A few more moves take you to the chains.
content.location: Immediately left of Mostly Labrador, route climbs right side of bulge. Start is in narrow alley between wall and rock pile with a good size tree growing.

content.description: Climbing on medium sized crimps and and pockets leads to the giant hole that is the namesake of the route. A big move to a jug and you can reach the chains.
content.location: In between Mickey's Crack and Glass Slippers. You can also identify it by the giant hole to on the left side of the wall.

content.description: Some people use tree stump to get started but it isn't necessary. Similar to other routes on this section of wall. Fun warmup.
Climb the right-facing dihedral to the small roof, then it seems like the crux is reaching high for hold(s) and clipping the anchor. Bolts are on right side of the corner.   May be 10d?

Start on the choss shelf above the trail near the large dry roots. Climb face up to tufa holds at bolt 2 (located underside of small roof). Two jugs allow for a high clip (bolt 3) before ascending on thin crimps through the crux in the middle of the vertical face. Clip another bolt (4) at the top of the face before standing up at the anchors on a ledge 5 feet below the cliff top.
content.protection: 4 bolts plus 2 anchors with sport clips

content.description: Fun climb shares two bolts with Corscicane Brothers.  Follow the left line of bolts after that.   Crux is the middle of the face on slopey crimpy ledges.  Tougher for shorter people
Climb through a bolt to the break. Three more bolts on fairly pocketed rock. Cool crux hold. Finish left of roof.
Two small roofs, throw a heel or champ your way over the edge to a great crimp. Whale over the top to anchors.
content.location: 3rd line from the left on Cheech and Chong. Starts on easy, pocketed, colorful rock to the left of a prominent black streak.

content.description: Clip first bolt, climb left of it and surmount the dusty ledge. Climb up slightly overhanging section using 'mail slots' on right or crimpers on left.  Reach across to the right and get into jugs going up a faint arete that overhangs and gets your forearms pumped.  Clip the anchor.
content.location: Right of Up In Smoke.  Route farthest right on this wall.

content.description: Clip first bolt (if you want) to get on the ledge, then clip second bolt and veer rightward clipping several more bolts past two huecos and an 'elephant trunk' to the anchor.
content.location: Left of the center portion of the wall.  Shares first two bolts with Highter.

content.description: A lot of quality routes here. The wall is a little ugly from a distance.
